This is one of the most challenging hack-n-slash RPGs I've ever played, and 
I do love a challenge. The way we're able to develop the characters is 
certainly something I haven't yet seen in another RPG. There is 
inconsistent looping of the BGMs, but it doesn't become too much of a 
hassle especially when you're focused on fighting. What does become too 
much of a hassle, though, is the imperfect dialogue throughout the game. 
There are far too many errors to follow along with, what seems to me like, 
such a great story. There's also an issue with the Quest section of the 
Menu. Things look okay at first, but eventually that section becomes all 
jumbled up and I can't check the details of my quests. I've had to restart 
the app every time this happens.

Well, the English translation is appalling to say the least, 80% of the sentences make no sense whatsoever, I take it it was directly translated from the particular expressions of the native language. Storyline-wise its not terrible, however most events don't have a clear correlation to the line and there are points where the two characters seem to be very out of sync from one another, also, there are several very important plot blanks. What happened to Ray's Sister? What has become of Ramirez (that's actually the stupidest name I've ever seen given to a princess)? Have the protagonists ever encounter and figure out that Victor(Vitora) is actually their friend in disguise? What about the Shadow Union? I've finished the game, and after you beat Ignit (twice), do the characters just sod off in blissful ignorance of all the events that were left unsolved? Also, why doesn't the game keep our progress in the end, instead of resetting to the beginning only with higher levels? And one more thing, Kainen is severely underpowered when compared to Ray at the same lvl with the same equivalent skills.  I hope to see a second game to this, but please, make it decent before releasing it.
